{"parentUuid":"814c8b48-3fc1-40d4-9399-042fe94b4bea","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa907e1b1860661b5","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccs99usGMwEkEC39rCKXB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018bCZccBGF41BVQbEq4Tgpm","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd \"C:/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test\" && echo \"=====acceptance AC16=====\" && grep -n -i \"middleware\\|pure.asgi\\|follow\\|AC16\\|3000\\|500\" docs/decisions/feature/usage-export/acceptance.md | head -40 && echo \"=====run-summary followup=====\" && grep -n -i \"middleware\\|follow\\|escalat\\|pure.asgi\" docs/decisions/feature/usage-export/run-summary.json | head","description":"Check acceptance and run-summary for middleware follow-up"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1336,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3746,"cache_read_input_tokens":32251,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3746,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs99tKkPKKgBGaWhG8Fg","attributionAgent":"Explore","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"a823683d-b64b-46b9-9038-feeaa04059c5","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:49:08.796Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"a823683d-b64b-46b9-9038-feeaa04059c5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"aa907e1b1860661b5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018bCZccBGF41BVQbEq4Tgpm","type":"tool_result","content":"=====acceptance AC16=====\n10:  a reporting route with a documented p95 sanity check (AC16); the binding perf constraint is the\n28:| AC11 | Response headers: `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8`; `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=usage-export-<UTC timestamp>.csv` (no tenant identifier in filename); inherits `nosniff` + `Cache-Control: no-store` | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/api/middleware.py` | Integration header assertions (incl. filename pattern, no tenant id) |\n33:| AC16 | Performance budget: export route **p95 <= 3,000 ms at the 100,000-row cap** (integration timing sanity — NOT a k6 load AC). *[Human-confirmed at the 2026-07-09 debugging escalation, resolving plan Open Q1: the proposed 500 ms is unreachable within the approved constant-memory streaming design (irreducible ~0.85–1.0 s cursor+encoding floor; optimized p95 2.07 s stable at the cap). 500 ms would require a design change (buffered fetch or lower cap) and is recorded as aspiration, not budget.]* | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration timing sanity test at ~100k rows asserting the <= 3,000 ms bound |\n39:| AC22 | Safe-error / fail-closed pre-flight: a forced internal error during the pre-flight `prepare_export` `COUNT` phase (before any response byte) returns the generic `500 internal` error-envelope (no stack/SQL/internal path leaked), rolls back the transaction, and starts **no** stream / emits **no** partial CSV body (ASVS 16.5.x). Distinct from plan §R3 (post-200 mid-stream truncation, accepted) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/api/errors.py`, `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Unit in `tests/test_usage_export_service.py` (non-cap DB error propagates, not swallowed, no stream started) + integration in `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` (forced pre-flight `COUNT` error → `500 internal` envelope, no leak, no partial body) |\n=====run-summary followup=====","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"aa934f8c-2bb1-4e14-b417-e0f9f3ecb1e1","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:49:09.116Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a823683d-b64b-46b9-9038-feeaa04059c5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
